text.tspan: To submit data to the portal, contact
tbsequencing@who.int to request an
account creation.
Validate your email address
via the received invitation.
Create a new package using
the data submission page.
Using the provided template, upload your Minimum
Inhibitory Concentration (MIC) values or phenotypic
Drug Resistance Test (pDST) results. Use NCBI/EBI
identification labels if the sequencing data is publicly
available.
Sequencing data information
Profile validation
Registration
Package creation
Resistance data uploading
Package sending
Package approval
Data matching
Our database is synchronized daily with the
submissions available at the NCBI/EBI. Thus if
the sequencing data you want to submit is
already publicly available there, you do not
need to upload it again. Otherwise provide all
fastq.gz files through the package entry.
Sample labels in the rows of your MIC or pDST data
will need to be matched to the sequencing data.
NCBI/EBI identifiers will be matched automatically if
they are available in the public record. If the sample
labels you used are different than the file names of
the sequencing data you uploaded, you can use the
FASTQ Prefix column from the MIC/pDST template to
match them appropriately. Use the Match button on
the package entry to perform the matching.
Once matching has been performed, you can submit
your package entry. Before sending it to admin review,
you can provide collaborators names to be credited for
their contribution to the data generation and data
sharing.
Your package will now go through
admin review, and you will be notified
via email upon acceptance or rejection.
If you want to submit data to the
portal, contact tbsequencing@who.int
to request an account creation.
